HEADWORD: Sculler
<hw>Scull"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A boat
rowed by one man with two sculls, or short oars.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who sculls.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scullery</ent>⟦br⟧
